# Angular templates

- Use Angular v21 **control flow** syntax (`@if`, `@for`, …) where the repo already uses it (see `App` template).
- Treat signals as functions in templates (`selectedUser()`, `users()`); don’t read `.value`.
- Prefer “thin templates”: avoid complex inline logic; move computations to `computed()` or component methods.
- Keep inputs/outputs explicit and readable (one binding per line when it improves clarity).

## Formatting

- Prettier HTML parser is `angular`; keep formatting stable (don’t fight auto-format).

## Accessibility basics

- Keep interactive elements semantic (`button` for actions); if using non-semantic elements, add keyboard + ARIA support.
